
[1]loyal

   LOY'AL, a. [L. lex, law.]

   Faithful to a prince or superior; true to plighted faith, duty or love;
   not treacherous; used of subjects to their prince, and of husband, wife
   and lovers; as a loyal subject; a loyal wife.

   There Laodamia with Evadne moves, unhappy both! but loyal in their
   loves.
